Finding balance in an unbalanced world. 
Taking time to connect with your internal world through meditation can be one of the greatest gifts you can give yourself. Meditation does not have to be a formal practice where you sit cross legged and clear your mind of all thoughts. It can be as simple as taking 3 long breaths, going for walk with you dog, listening to music or working out. Mediation is fundamentally about bringing your focused attention into the present moment, even if it’s brief. 

A very simple technique I use with my clients who are just beginning a meditation practice is box breathing:
- 4 second inhale through the nose. 
- 4 second hold 
- 4 second exhale through the mouth 
- 4 second hold

Try this for 3 rounds and then observe how your body feels. And just like that you’ve meditated 🧘🏻‍♂️ #koioshealthcoaching

Sunsets have long been regarded as a metaphor for new beginnings. As the sun descends beyond the horizon, painting the sky with a myriad of vibrant colors, it symbolizes the end of one chapter and the dawn of another. Just as every sunset holds the promise of a new day, it reminds us that even after the darkest times, there is always hope for a fresh start. Sunsets teach us the invaluable lesson of embracing change, letting go of the past, and embracing the unknown with optimism. They serve as a gentle reminder that no matter how challenging life may be, there is beauty in every ending, and new beginnings await those who are willing to embrace them. The stillness is also my favorite time of day to photograph.

Life often presents us with challenging times that feel like stumbling blocks, it’s how I’ve been feeling the past 6 months after an injury and then surgery. It is during these moments of hardship that we have the opportunity to showcase our resilience. As we gather the fragments of lost hopes for where we thought life was going we discover the power within us to rebuild, reinvent, and reimagine our lives. That is where my attention is now focused, on all the possibilities that lie ahead. #daybyday

In times of profound sadness and loss, nature often becomes a sanctuary for the hurting soul. The gentle rustle of leaves in the forest or the rhythmic crashing of waves on a shore provide a soothing backdrop, welcoming reflection and peace. 

With all the loss and turmoil we are experiencing at this moment in history, give yourself the time and space to connect with nature, even in the smallest way, to take a breath and get grounded. 

To move past these challenging times it is up to us to think clearly and critically and avoid the cycle of cynicism and fear. Those emotions only contribute to the collective suffering.

Nick & Sean lead with a clear vision on design and function which resulted in a well balanced space that is sophisticated and modern while still feeling very casual and comfortable. With a vast art collection the curation of work thoughtout gives added layers of texture and color that makes the entire house feel unified, cohesive and full of interest.
